name: py-performance
description:
The performance project is intended to be an authoritative source of
benchmarks for all Python implementations. The focus is on real-world
benchmarks, rather than synthetic benchmarks, using whole applications
when possible.

dependencies.name: py-pip
dependencies.description: The PyPA recommended tool for installing Python packages.

dependencies.name: py-setuptools
dependencies.description:
A Python utility that aids in the process of downloading, building,
upgrading, installing, and uninstalling Python packages.

dependencies.name: py-pyperf
dependencies.description:
The Python perf module is a toolkit to write, run and analyze
benchmarks.
